1:1
2021
4950x4950px

I wanted to use a palette that was perhaps broader than before but that was made of ‘natural’ colours. The yellow/gold was stolen from the previous work and that made me think about this time of year. Harvests and grey skies and berries in the hedgerows and the fields turning from green to brown.

I spent a lot of time in the countryside of beautiful Derbyshire in England when I was a kid. I think it’s had a lasting impression. Thankfully.

I’m aware that digital art, particularly NFTart doesn’t tend to cover this type of ground, yet.
